  479: init_per_suite(suite) ->
  480:     [];
  481: init_per_suite(doc) ->
  482:     [];
  483: init_per_suite(Config0) when is_list(Config0) ->
  484: 
  485:     ?ANNOUNCE_SUITE_INIT(),
  486: 
  487:     p("init_per_suite -> entry with"
  488:       "~n      Config: ~p"
  489:       "~n      Nodes:  ~p", [Config0, erlang:nodes()]),
  490: 
  491:     case ?LIB:init_per_suite(Config0) of
  492:         {skip, _} = SKIP ->
  493:             SKIP;
  494: 
  495:         Config1 when is_list(Config1) ->
  496: 
  497:             %% We need a (local) monitor on this node also
  498:             megaco_test_sys_monitor:start(),
  499: 
  500:             p("init_per_suite -> end when"
  501:               "~n      Config: ~p"
  502:               "~n      Nodes:  ~p", [Config1, erlang:nodes()]),
  503: 
  504:             Config1
  505:     end.
  506: 
  507: end_per_suite(suite) -> [];
  508: end_per_suite(doc) -> [];
  509: end_per_suite(Config0) when is_list(Config0) ->
  510: 
  511:     ?ANNOUNCE_SUITE_END(),
  512: 
  513:     p("end_per_suite -> entry with"
  514:       "~n      Config: ~p"
  515:       "~n      Nodes:  ~p", [Config0, erlang:nodes()]),
  516: 
  517:     megaco_test_sys_monitor:stop(),
  518:     Config1 = ?LIB:end_per_suite(Config0),
  519: 
  520:     p("end_per_suite -> end when"
  521:       "~n      Nodes:  ~p", [erlang:nodes()]),
  522: 
  523:     Config1.
  524:

 4094: otp6490(Msg, Codec, Conf, ExpectedEncode, ExpectedDecode) ->
 4095:     case (catch encode_message(Codec, Conf, Msg)) of
 4096:         {error, _Reason} when ExpectedEncode =:= error ->
 4097:             ok;
 4098:         {error, Reason} when ExpectedEncode =:= ok ->
 4099:             exit({unexpected_encode_failure, Reason});
 4100:         {ok, Bin} when ExpectedEncode =:= error ->
 4101:             exit({unexpected_encode_success, Msg, binary_to_list(Bin)});
 4102:         {ok, Bin} when ExpectedEncode =:= ok ->
 4103:             case decode_message(Codec, false, Conf, Bin) of
 4104:                 {ok, Msg} when ExpectedDecode == ok ->
 4105:                     ok;
 4106:                 {ok, Msg} when ExpectedDecode =:= error ->
 4107:                     exit({unexpected_decode_success, Msg});
 4108:                 {ok, Msg2} when ExpectedDecode =:= ok ->
 4109:                     exit({unexpected_decode_result, Msg, Msg2});
 4110:                 {ok, Msg2} when ExpectedDecode =:= error ->
 4111:                     exit({unexpected_decode_success, Msg, Msg2});
 4112:                 {error, _Reason} when ExpectedDecode =:= error ->
 4113:                     ok;

 4271: otp7671(Msg, Codec, Conf, ExpectedEncode, ExpectedDecode) ->
 4272:     Check = fun(M1, M2) -> 
 4273: 		    exit({unexpected_decode_result, M1, M2})
 4274: 	    end,
 4275:     otp7671(Msg, Codec, Conf, ExpectedEncode, ExpectedDecode, Check).

 4277: otp7671(Msg, Codec, Conf, ExpectedEncode, ExpectedDecode, Check) ->
 4278:     case (catch encode_message(Codec, Conf, Msg)) of
 4279:         {error, _Reason} when ExpectedEncode =:= error ->
 4280:             ok;
 4281:         {error, Reason} when ExpectedEncode =:= ok ->
 4282:             exit({unexpected_encode_failure, Reason});
 4283:         {ok, Bin} when ExpectedEncode =:= error ->
 4284:             exit({unexpected_encode_success, Msg, binary_to_list(Bin)});
 4285:         {ok, Bin} when ExpectedEncode =:= ok ->
 4286:             case decode_message(Codec, false, Conf, Bin) of
 4287:                 {ok, Msg} when ExpectedDecode =:= ok ->
 4288: 		    io:format("otp7671 -> decoded:identical~n", []),
 4289:                     ok;
 4290:                 {ok, Msg2} when ExpectedDecode =:= ok ->
 4291: 		    Check(Msg, Msg2);
 4292:                 {ok, Msg} when ExpectedDecode =:= error ->
 4293:                     exit({unexpected_decode_success, Msg});
 4294:                 {ok, Msg2} when ExpectedDecode =:= error ->
 4295:                     exit({unexpected_decode_success, Msg, Msg2});
 4296:                 {error, _Reason} when ExpectedDecode =:= error ->
 4297:                     ok;
 4298:                 {error, Reason} when ExpectedDecode == ok ->
 4299:                     exit({unexpected_decode_failure, Msg, Reason})
 4300:             end
 4301:     end.

 4383: expect_codec(Expect, Codec, Msg, Conf) ->
 4384:     t("expect_codec -> entry with"
 4385:       "~n   Expect: ~p"
 4386:       "~n   Msg:    ~p", [Expect, Msg]),
 4387:     case (catch encode_message(Codec, Conf, Msg)) of
 4388: 	{error, _Reason} when Expect =:= error ->
 4389:  	    d("expect_codec -> encode failed as expected"
 4390: 	      "~n   _Reason: ~w", [_Reason]),
 4391: 	    ok;
 4392: 	{error, Reason} ->
 4393:  	    e("expect_codec -> encode failed unexpectedly: "
 4394: 	      "~n   Reason: ~w", [Reason]),
 4395: 	    exit({unexpected_encode_result, Reason});
 4396: 	{ok, Bin} when Expect =:= error ->
 4397:  	    e("expect_codec -> encode succeded unexpectedly: "
 4398: 	      "~n   ~w", [binary_to_list(Bin)]),
 4399: 	    exit({unexpected_encode_result, binary_to_list(Bin)});
 4400: 	{ok, Bin} ->
 4401: 	    d("expect_codec -> successfull encode as expected:"
 4402: 	      "~n~s", [binary_to_list(Bin)]),
 4403: 	    case (catch decode_message(Codec, false, Conf, Bin)) of
 4404: 		{ok, Msg} ->
 4405:  		    d("expect_codec -> successfull decode~n", []),
 4406: 		    ok;
 4407: 		{ok, Msg2} ->
 4408:  		    e("expect_codec -> successfull decode"
 4409: 		      " - but not equal", []),
 4410: 		    chk_MegacoMessage(Msg, Msg2);
 4411: 		%% exit({unexpected_decode_result, Msg, Msg2});
 4412: 		Else ->
 4413:  		    e("expect_codec -> decode failed:~n~p", [Else]),
 4414: 		    exit({unexpected_decode_result, Else})
 4415: 	    end;
 4416: 	Else ->
 4417: 	    e("expect_codec -> encode failed:~n~p", [Else]),
 4418: 	    exit({unexpected_encode_result, Else})
 4419:     end.
